history.content: Do you have another course you're planning to enroll in? I've heard that it's hard to find one that will accept students this late.

children.subject: You tagged your post as both "EECS" and "CS"; which college are you? The two have different minimum unit requirements (13 for L&S, 12 for CoE), and so I can't tell if it's possible for you to simply drop without adding another course or not.
I'm in EECS. So I suppose it would be possible to drop, then?
If you have 12 or more units, then you're fine.

Great point Steven. Yes, the system will not let you drop a course if it would put you below your unit requirement. Since your EECS, you could just drop it, if you were L&S, you would not be able to w/o first enrolling in a 1+ unit course.

I don't, because I thought I would be able to handle this course, but I'm finding that I probably won't be able to. I don't really remember the required prerequisite knowledge and most of the class is flying straight over my head. 

I'm really not sure what to do now.

history.content:
I have 16 units right now, 4 of those are P/NP. I'm realizing that one of the EECS classes I'm taking will be a bit much for this semester, so I'm considering switching out.

However, I'm not sure if that's a good idea - I assume I would receive no credit for any homework or assignments done in the first few weeks of class. This alone would be a huge hit to my grade/GPA.
history.subject: Is it feasible to switch classes this late in the semester?
